title: Album Page, "Mills in Marshy Landscape", possibly 1887
medium: Brush and watercolor, graphite on thick off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: recto, in graphite, upper left corner: 42; upper right corner (inscribed in a circle): 38
description: Horizontal sheet tipped vertically into binding.  Seen from a distance are a group of brown mills.  In the foreground is a body of water, its shallows punctuated by small groups of grasses, which become more dense in the direction of the mills.  The sky is thick with dark grey clouds at the horizon.
